Notes on a rewrite


17 Mar 2012 01:13






Okay. Let me start by saying that I really like the idea of a Foundation administrator having been turned into this object, but retaining his sapience, personality, and ability to communicate.

One detail that really bugs me, though, is the idea that his dedicated devoted staff would have hidden this from the rest of the Foundation for decades. This guy has like level-4 clearance, and now he's turned into an SCP, and he continues performing administrative duties? No.

I want him to do the responsible thing. I want him to report himself.

I want him to have been originally classified as Safe, but he argued that he's obviously sapient, and we have no idea what he's truly capable of, or how a human mind can be functional in this form, so he should be Euclid.

He makes himself available as a consulting zoologist, but only on non-anomalous subjects.

Hmm.

Perhaps he's not just the telephone, but the full set of 1970s office machinery  typewriter, desk chair, calculator, etc. That would make it easier for us to give him clerical work.



some of the level 4s are pondering whether he's being too conscientious to be human, but isn't conscientiousness a /good// thing? If he is an alien intelligence that's pretending to be Dr Office-Machinery, it's doing exactly what the Foundation would want Dr Office-Machinery to do in this situation.







